Hepatitis A - Russia: update (01) 13 Feb 2001 20010214.0291
Date: 7 Mar 2001 12:30:58 -0500
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ITAR/TASS News Agency, 7 Mar 2001 06:12 AM EST [edited

VLADIVOSTOK: A total of 44 people has contracted hepatitis A virus
infection in the Trudovoye settlement which is part of the Vladivostok
municipality. Of these 19 are children.
The press office of the Vladivostok administration told Itar-Tass that
sanitary experts had found hepatitis A virus was present in the main water
supply. Specialists believe that the virus had got into the mains directly
from the [source of the supply.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This is a further indication of the infrastructure problems afflicting
Russia at the present time; on this occasion affecting the far eastern
region of Russia. - Mod.CP
